reviews.ReviewText: This cereal was delicious I am a 55 year old man and I bought these because they said they had a lot of fiber for my little tummy and it helped me learn to count and this wasn’t even the only cereal I got the froot loops, trix, fruity pebbles, and fruity pebbles with marshmallows were extra fruity I loved them. The coco puffs were so coco when they made my milk chocolate I got so excited. The dunkaroos were so good I got 2 boxes they were extra dunky. The apple jacks might have been my favorite they were so good they were extra apple flavored. The captain crunch was so crunch I loved it. The rice crispeses were so good I was and when I poured the milk in i got so excited it was making a sound like snap crackle pop. The corn pops they were the first one i had and they were so good. Frosted Flakes and cookie crisp was so good I loved them the the cookies were so good in the cookie crisp. The lucky charms are no magic treasures but they were magically delicious and they were even better on saint patricks day i just wish i bought the ones that turn the milk green. The oreos were so good. I can’t forget about the cinnamon roll frosted mini wheats. The only problem is that I just ate 17 boxes of cereal in 3 weeks.

reviews.Title: Mr.
reviews.ReviewText: After reading a few articles about how General Mills is returning to original formulations for some of their classic brands I was hoping Kellogg's would do the same for some of my favorite Kellogg's brands I had stopped buying years ago because of flavor and texture changes. On impulse I picked up a box of Apple Jacks which I hadn't done in 20 years thinking maybe they had reverted back to the vintage formulas. Dumb idea. Nothing's changed. In fact they were even worse. Smaller, no crunch and very insipid flavor with no cinnamon to speak of. I'm sure Froot Loops are still no better. as well. Cereal sales are TANKING, Kellogg's. Have you ever considered that you're your own worst enemy? Bring back the ORIGINALS!

reviews.Title: what happened?
reviews.ReviewText: I bought Apple Jacks for the first time in a year or so and my family (four of us; two adults and two adults) and I could immediately tell that something had changed about them. They seemed lighter in density, less sweet, less intensely flavored. Did Kellogg's change the recipe in some way? They're simply not as tasty as they used to be and didn't really taste that different from all those bland, "limited edition" cereals based on movies or whatever that appear briefly on the shelves. I can't see buying them again and I hope you restore their original recipe. If I'm wrong, and the cereal recipe hasn't been tampered with recently, please let me know. I was reminded of how Post Honeycomb seemed to have changed for the worse, we stopped buying them, and then a few years ago restored their "original flavor" and now all is right with the world.

reviews.Title: Best Healthy Cereal Out There!
reviews.ReviewText: Scrumptious, healthy cereal with a perfect blend of whole grain crunchy flakes, sliced almonds, and fruit. Plus you get a sweet surprise of vanilla clusters every once in awhile. It's packed with 5 grams per cup of dietary fiber, which is difficult to find in cereal! There is no high fructose corn syrup, no cholesterol, and it's low in fat. It's a great source of Calcium, and Vitamin D (which you need here in upstate NY due to the lack of sunshine). I eat it with soymilk and on occasion, I will throw in a dash or two of cinnamon and stir. Delicious! I feel energized after eating it, instead of that sluggish feeling you get when you eat something that's not good for you. I was worried when I couldn't find it in the store for awhile, but I think that's because they changed from a 16oz box to a 19.8. So happy they didn't discontinue it! Thank you, General Mills!

The only thing I wish they could replace is the hydrogenated oils since they are not healthy at all, I know it's coconut oil but still hydrogenated. However, it's a small amount and I don't eat cereal daily so once in a while won't hurt much. Kudos for improving your product, now I can have some childhood nostalgia when I have a bowl of pops.

reviews.Title: Inferior to the old version
reviews.ReviewText: I used to LOVE Cracklin Oat Bran so I bought 10 boxes at the grocery store. However, I am so disappointed. I think they changed the recipe. It has much less flavor than it used to. It is much sweeter but has less molasses/cinnamon flavor. It's not as crispy and doesn't stay firm in milk as well. I also don't think the bran is as pronounced so the texture isn't as solid after it sits for a while. It used to taste like gingerbread but now it's missing mang of the spices. I don't get the nice clove and nutmeg taste I used to. Very sad. It's very unhealthy--high in calories or fat--but that didn't used to matter since it tasted so good. Now that it's not as delicious, it's not really worth eating.

reviews.Title: Does not taste good anymore
reviews.ReviewText: I've been buying the bags for a long time and all of a sudden the cereal taste bad. I thought maybe it was a stale bag but the next couple where the same. I took a break for a couple months and bought a small box and it tasted great. The next week I went back to the big bag and it was horrible again. If it doesn't change back they lost a long time customer

reviews.Title: I am disappointed
reviews.ReviewText: I am very disappointed because they change the recipe and now it really taste bad. I understand if it wasn't healthy or whatever but it taste better the old way nothing away I won't even eat it anymore.

reviews.Title: My favorite
reviews.ReviewText: This has been one of my favorite cereals since I was a kid... Yummy fruit flavors

reviews.Title: Our family favorite cereal.
reviews.ReviewText: Fruity pebbles is the best cereal. I buy it often cause it never last long in my house. We eat it normally and we like to use it for other things like making our own cereal bars. It's amazing!!

reviews.Title: I will buy this cereal for the rest of my life
reviews.ReviewText: This cereal is a must in my house. It's been my favorite since I was a child, and now it's my 2 year olds favorite as well! We love the sweet fruity flavor, and we enjoy making breakfast bars out of them as well! This is truly a delicious and nostalgic breakfast miracle!

reviews.Title: Will continue buying
reviews.ReviewText: My family loves fruity pebbles. I buy a box almost everytime I go to the store. I just wish it didn't get soggy as fast as it does!

reviews.Title: Childhood favorite
reviews.ReviewText: This has always been a favorite of mine, since I was a child. The colors, the smell, the versatility, it has it all! I liked that it changes my milk a fun color too! I use this cereal for more than just a breakfast go too. I use it to make sweet treats for the family too!

reviews.Title: Fruity Pebbles Review.
reviews.ReviewText: Fruity Pebbles are absolutely delicious, it's one of my all time favorite cereals. Bright pretty color, great crunch, holds up great against milk but I can't lie I like when they get a bit soggy. Great for kids and adults. This cereal I HIGHLY recommend. Also gluten free.

reviews.Title: New Flavor is Gross
reviews.ReviewText: Updated flavor is not good at all. Just STOP.

reviews.Title: Love this product!
reviews.ReviewText: My entire family eats this. It's our favorite!

reviews.Title: Most tasty cereal I have ever had
reviews.ReviewText: The way the melt in your mouth with taste is just so amazing. The only problems I have with them is they get soggy really fast so if that could be improved that would make it way better. And the fact that over the past years I have eaten them the amount of cereal they have in the boxes have gone down but with that I have no problems with this amazing cereal.

reviews.Title: One of my favorite cereals ! Definitely will buy good ..
reviews.ReviewText: I love the fruit taste ! We've made fruity people treats .. my elementary teacher used to make them and to this day they're sooo good .. all so it's one of the first cereals I look for in the cereal aisle

reviews.Title: Put it on everything
reviews.ReviewText: I love using them to make crispy treats and on top of ice cream. Very tasty and a unique texture

reviews.Title: Love
reviews.ReviewText: These are so yummy and sweet! Great for kids and adults! Lots of flavor!

reviews.Title: Love this cereal
reviews.ReviewText: Love this cereal and eat it more as a snack rather than breakfast cereal.

reviews.Title: Best Cereal Ever!!!
reviews.ReviewText: Fruity Pebbles cereal has been my favorite cereal since I was a little kid. I am 41 now and I still buy Fruity Pebbles now for my family. It is just very flavorable and so yummy.

reviews.Title: I love this product.
reviews.ReviewText: I love Fruity Pebbles. It is one of my favorite cereals from Post Consumer Brands! Whenever I have a box, it is gone within days. I really love how small the "pebbles" are because it makes it easier to eat the cereal. The only problem with this is that it gets soggy very quickly in milk.

reviews.Title: No I will not buy this product again
reviews.ReviewText: My daughter told me these fruity pebbles taste like rice crispys had to try it myself hu yuck it's a totally the new cereal might as well change the name.

reviews.Title: Go back to the original taste!
reviews.ReviewText: I'm not sure if maybe I just bought a stale box from the grocery store or.. they just completely changed how they make Fruity Pebbles. I'm currently eating a bowl right now and it tastes bland. Not fruity at all like it used to taste! They're also puffier? Not a fan of that. This used to be one of my favorite cereals but now I just might stop buying if it continues to taste like this. Please go back! I swear they were amazing just 6 months ago when I last had a bowl before this bland one today. I'll give it 5 stars once it tastes right again.

reviews.Title: It's so bad now!
reviews.ReviewText: They changed the recipe and now it's just awful. Like others have said, they're just flavorless, colored rice krispies now. My favorite cereal for forty years, ruined....

reviews.Title: I cant beleive they changed the formula
reviews.ReviewText: The cereal was perfect. The new formula tastes just like rice krispies cereal. It tastes 10 times worse than before. If it isnt broke dont fix it. So yall are just trying to save money with cheaper cereal? Well I'm not buying FP next time at the store because they are ruined now... I'm so sad

reviews.Title: This USED to be my favorite cereal
reviews.ReviewText: Even as an adult, I eat this cereal religiously. Several days ago I bought 2 boxes as per my usual. Both were like neon Rice Krispies! Why did you change this reliable favorite?!! It's like small puffy trix. You've ruined them.

reviews.Title: Breakfast in a hurry
reviews.ReviewText: Surely not the healthiest breakfast option but I bet your kids will love them.

reviews.Title: I buy this product 5 to 6 times a week.
reviews.ReviewText: Ok I've been eating fruity pebbles since I was 10 I'm about to turn 32 here on the 24th. Lately I've been pretty upset with post and the fruity pebbles. Because they are not the same fruity pebbles I've been eating my whole life. The fruity pebbles I've been buying are more like rice crispy cereal instead of fruity pebbles. I love my normal fruity pebbles and its very upsetting that I go to the store to buy my midnight snack (fruity pebbles) and when I get home and it's about 12 1 am and the cereal looks like flavored rice crispy cereal and it really makes me mad that I spent my money on cereal that I refuse to eat because it's not the orginal fruity pebbles. So what I'm getting to is please please bring my orginal fruity pebbles back please.

reviews.Title: I love Fruity pebbles
reviews.ReviewText: I love fruity pebbles so much but now when I buy the cereal its not crispy and airy its poofy last week I bought the small bowl fruity pebbles and it was light and crispy cereal but the box is poofy i don't want to ever stop eating my only favorite cereal but can whoever makes fruity pebbles fix it because I know its not supposed to be like that I've been eating this cereal since i was 4 and I know what it suppose to look like and taste like and poofy ain't it

reviews.Title: Love this Nostalgic Cereal!
reviews.ReviewText: Love this stuff; such a classic! It’s a perfectly fruity and nostalgic cereal.
My granddaughters love this cereal

reviews.Title: Worth the money and they cost less then other stores
reviews.ReviewText: They taste very good :) highly recommend
It fell but not your falt but anyway it’s good
Too sugary but they are a classic cereal
I love this cereal! It tastes great on its own, in milk, and it is very versatile! Highly recommend.
Best cereal ever and you can make so many fun stuff with them as well!

reviews.Title: YUM!
reviews.ReviewText: Love this for breakfast, a snack or a frozen yogurt topping.  Fun to make treat bars with too!  Can't ever keep it in the pantry because everyone loves it!

reviews.Title: Good Stuff!
reviews.ReviewText: It’s as tasty as you remember.

reviews.Title: Review of Golden Grahams
reviews.ReviewText: Good cereal good change of pace from Cherrios.
I absolutely love Golden Grahams.

reviews.Title: Long-standing favorite
reviews.ReviewText: Nutty flavor and a small amount goes a long way. Great for breakfast or with a little honey on ice cream - or as a little crunch on salad.

reviews.Title: Very good but why so high in sodium!
reviews.ReviewText: I've always loved grape-nuts but can't eat them anymore because they're so high in sodium. Why can't the sodium level be reduced or even offer a low-sodium version? By the time you eat 1-cup with milk, you've had about 40% of the daily 2000mg sodium limit as recommended by the American Heart Association.

reviews.Title: Great product!
reviews.ReviewText: This cereal is always delicious. It is a great staple to have in the pantry!

reviews.Title: This is the classic all time healthy breakfast cereal.
reviews.ReviewText: Grapenuts cereal is great with blueberries and milk. I also like to make cereal bars with oatmeal, grapenuts, applesauce, and dried fruit or chocolate chips. In college, grape nuts muffins and grape nuts with yogurt were my introduction.

reviews.Title: Sad Canadian
reviews.ReviewText: I have been looking for Post Grape-Nuts for a couple of years without success. I found out that this cereal has been discontinued in Canada. Does anyone know if it can be purchased online and shipped to a Canadian address?

reviews.Title: yummy
reviews.ReviewText: I like it mostly as granola with yogurt parfaits, very yummy!

reviews.Title: Healthy and Delicious!
reviews.ReviewText: Delicious cereal. It’s versatile too! I enjoy it hot with berries on top.

reviews.Title: Grape nuts is great
reviews.ReviewText: Five stars for availability , price and ease of ordering with no shipping because I have the target card . And i greatly appreciate speaking with a very pleasant English speaking representative

reviews.Title: Old Favorite
reviews.ReviewText: I was surprised to find my grocery store out of the G-Nuts. Not that they're prominently displayed: bottom shelf, 1 row deep. I read the article in the paper about the short supply and freaked out. I even tried Grape Nuts Flakes....definitely not the same or even close. A couple of days ago I managed to procure 2 boxes (thats not hoarding, is it?) and I plan to enjoy my stash with 2% milk and maple syrup as has been my custom for many years.

reviews.Title: My morning staple!!!
reviews.ReviewText: Okay, I get the toilet paper shortage during COVID, but Grape Nuts?!? Where are you located? I will come to work on the assembly line. Should my rating be based on the shortage? ZERO! Or the product?

reviews.Title: Only cereal my doctor doesn't say not to eat
reviews.ReviewText: I love the taste of Grape Nuts (Original). I love the crunch. And no added sugar plus high fiber makes this the best of all cereals for healthy eating. Stores have been out of stock for a month - pushing the flakes. I tried the flakes but much prefer the Original Grape Nuts.

reviews.Title: Love this cereal
reviews.ReviewText: I simply love this cereal. It is great by itself or in your favorite yogurt. I am shocked to not find it in San Antonio. They are selling it online for over $100! I love it but not for $100. So not sure where to find them. Cereal is my all time favorite since my 20's, 30's and now 40's. Yum.

reviews.Title: I love this cereal
reviews.ReviewText: I love grape nuts. Love it with my yogurt

reviews.Title: Grape Nuts not flakes
reviews.ReviewText: Difficult to find grape nuts, stores are out of stock.

reviews.Title: Forget spinach, grape nuts is where the iron is at
reviews.ReviewText: I am a regular blood donor and I try to give every 56 days but I tend to have trouble keeping my iron up even with iron supplements. The absolute only thing that has worked for me is eating a serving of Grape-Nuts every day. For the first time last year I was able to donate every 56 days. I recently ran out of grape nuts and couldn't find any in the store so my next blood donation my iron was once again too low. Other than keeping my iron up grape nuts tastes great and are a filling snack.

reviews.Title: My absolute favorite cereal! Don't ever discontinue!
reviews.ReviewText: I've been eating Grape-Nuts since I was a kid so that's 50+ years now. I make hot Grape-Nuts: 1/2 c. G-N, 1/2 c. skim milk, 1 tsp. brown sugar, 1 tsp. butter, microwave, then total yumminess! Very disappointed that Grape-Nuts are really hard to find these days :(. I'm on my last box. Hope manufacturing picks up soon!

reviews.Title: Grape-Nuts are Great!
reviews.ReviewText: Post Grape Nuts has been one of my favorite cereals for years. The cereal is very filling and very low in sugar with a rich barley taste that keeps me coming back. It's hard to find quality, low-sugar cereals from the major brands these days but thankfully Post is still making Grape Nuts. The flake version is fantastic as well!

reviews.Title: What a crunch
reviews.ReviewText: I hadn't eaten grape nuts for years. Then I started putting them in vanilla yogurt. Let them sit for several minutes and they aren't so crunchy. This elevates them to an "adult cereal". The nutty flavor can not be beat.

reviews.Title: Great cereal!
reviews.ReviewText: I love grape nuts,they are a tasty cereal.

reviews.Title: One of my favorites.
reviews.ReviewText: I prefer to eat them hot with just a touch of sugar. Try it, you won't be disappointed.

reviews.Title: My All-Time Favorite!
reviews.ReviewText: This has been my favorite cereal since I was a little girl. Crunchy, filling, tasty, versatile, and good for you! No guilt after eating this hearty bowl of goodness. It can be enjoyed cold, with dairy or nut milk, but I also like it hot from time to time. It's a great replacement for oatmeal or farina, although I sometimes mix Grape-Nuts into my hot cereal. One regular serving is more than enough to satisfy with prolonged energy. I like to add just enough milk to cover in a bowl, and microwave for about 90 seconds. The Grape-Nuts expand, absorb the milk, and soften, then you can add whatever you like to enhance them: cinnamon, fresh fruit, seeds, nuts, flax meal, etc... Grape-Nuts will always be my favorite!

reviews.Title: Still the same great taste I remember
reviews.ReviewText: I haven't had Grape Nuts since I was a kid. Just bought them about a week ago and torn into them yesterday. YES!!!

reviews.Title: Delicious
reviews.ReviewText: My husband has been craving grape nuts cereal, so I bought him a box. Now, both my daughters are in love with them too! I've gotten two more boxes since then. I guess this will be the new staple in our home. Healthy and delicious, can't go wrong!

reviews.Title: Reminds me of my childhood
reviews.ReviewText: I love Grape-nuts they remind me of the first time I ate grownup cereal. I love the crunch and the slightly sweet taste not just pure sugar like most cereal.

reviews.Title: Delicious and versatile. A true classic.
reviews.ReviewText: My all-time favorite cereal. Not only is it healthy with just four ingredients (and very low sugar) but it is versatile. You can eat it hot or cold, put it on ice cream or yogurt, or add fruit. I also would like to add that it is one of the few cereals that my incredibly sensitive stomach can handle (I have GI issues). It's more nourishing than sugary kids cereals and doesn't leave you feeling hungry after you eat it. I like to let it soften in whole milk for a bit and eat it with sliced banana. There's a reason Post has offered this cereal for over 100 years!

reviews.Title: Very Nice Cereal
reviews.ReviewText: Grape nuts, though neither grapes nor nuts, are delicious AND great for your health.
Great source of fiber. Satisfies our hunger. Kids like it for breakfast instead of the high sugar cereals. We like to add milk and warm it in the microwave

reviews.Title: loved these for years
reviews.ReviewText: Love them wonderful flavour.

reviews.Title: healthy and filling
reviews.ReviewText: Grape Nuts are sooo good! I enjoy the taste alone with milk but even better when I cut up a banana in my cereal. I can eat this for breakfast and stay totally full until lunch. There are few ingredients which is ideal.

reviews.Title: Been eating Grape Nuts for 40+ Years
reviews.ReviewText: My dad's favorite cereal when I was growing up and I thought I was big time when I got to eat it too! So good tasting and good for you. There are endless possibilities and recipes in which you can eat this cereal. I personally like it warmed up in the microwave with Almond or Oat Milk. Sometimes I mix it it with other granola cereals and add banana, berries, spiced apples, etc.

reviews.Title: Super healthy
reviews.ReviewText: I thought all cereal was unhealthy, until I researched Grape Nuts. Specifically, I was looking for a cereal high in iron (I'm prone to iron deficiency), low in sugar, and free of lots of unnecessary processed ingredients. This cereal is so healthy!! Since I started eating it, my digestion has improved so much!! As a traditional cereal, I eat it with a protein powder shake instead of cow's milk, and it's delicious! (And FULL of protein!) By itself, I add it to peanut butter sandwiches, salads and basically anything where I crave a crunchy texture.
Husband loves these has a bowl everyday after work.

reviews.Title: It is not as Remembered
reviews.ReviewText: A bit disappointing...not terrible, just not as good as I remembered them tasting, but it has been well over 10 years.

reviews.Title: Tips to make you a Grape-Nuts lover!
reviews.ReviewText: Wholesome, minimally processed & delicious. I stir in a bit of brown sugar and contrary to all other cereals, I let this one soak up a bit of the milk before eating it. Still has a crunch without being 'hard'. Also good warmed in the microwave as an alternative to oatmeal!

reviews.Title: Great product!
reviews.ReviewText: Grape Nuts are really terrific - they have tons of iron (I think it's about 90% of your daily recommended value!) and they go very well with strawberries or blueberries in the morning. Don't start the day off bogged down with tons of sugar in your cereal or granola - have Grape Nuts and some fruit!

reviews.Title: I buy this product again and again
reviews.ReviewText: I have had this every morning for years and have never gotten sick of it. I LOVE GREAT GRAINS!!!

reviews.Title: I would and have bought this product again and again.
reviews.ReviewText: I love this product and will keep buying it often.
Great source of iron and fiber..... this is definitely a grown up cereal. There is no sugary taste.
Love the taste and texture. Always crisp and crunchy.

reviews.Title: This cereal is a winner!
reviews.ReviewText: The grains and pecans make a great combination. The pecans taste toasted and crunchy and are really nice size pieces. The grains taste slightly sweet and are delicious.

reviews.Title: Love the crunchy sweetness.
reviews.ReviewText: I love the combination in this cereal, the pecans add a special crunch and flavor. I think the pecan adds enough sweetness so no sugar is needed. My only complaint is I can not enough coupons..
great cereal! Shipped quickly

reviews.Title: Soggy mess
reviews.ReviewText: This cereal got soggy fairly quick, which made it disgusting. I won't be finishing the box.

reviews.Title: Healthy Crunchy Cereal
reviews.ReviewText: I really like the Great Grains crunchy pecan cereal. The flavor is amazing and stays crunchy in milk. I was worried I wouldn't like it because it's a healthy cereal but I've been eating it every morning. Only downfall is I haven't been able to find it on my area. Maybe when everything settles down I will be able to buy it.

reviews.Title: Great Grains stays crunchy
reviews.ReviewText: This cereal stays crunchy when adding milk. It has a great taste just a little bit of sweetness from the clusters. You get a good assortment of pecans, clusters and flakes. Very filling and tasty.

reviews.Title: Great taste, crunchy goodness
reviews.ReviewText: My husband and I both really like This cereal. Great taste, crunchy and filling!

reviews.Title: Are Great Grains really great! You bet they are!
reviews.ReviewText: I was lucky enough to receive a sample of Great Grains Crunchy Pecan cereal to try out and I'm so happy I was selected. This cereal is crunchy, packed with flavor and so satisfying! It keeps its crunch in milk and makes the ideal breakfast... or snack if you get hungry during the day. I love the whole grain texture and the added bonus of the pecans, which not only enhance the flavor but are also a great source of protein. My husband saw me eating it one morning and decided to give it a try. Now I'm lucky if there is any left for me! He's a real fan. Start your day out right with a bowl of great nutrition, flavor and crunch. You'll be glad you picked Great Grains Crunchy Pecan!

reviews.Title: Great taste and texture
reviews.ReviewText: I love that there's a variety of textures so it doesn't get soggy when you put milk on

reviews.Title: Filling and Nutrition Too!
reviews.ReviewText: I recently received a free sample of the Great Grains Crunchy Pecan cereal. I am not normally a cold cereal eater but decided to try it while I was working from home the last several weeks. My opinion of cold cereal is forever changed! The Crunchy Pecan was very filling! I wasn't searching for snacks all morning which was a change over my past routine. The cereal did not get soggy and I loved the crunch! I will definitely buy Great Grains Crunchy Pecan in the future!

reviews.Title: Post Great Grains Crunchy Pecan
reviews.ReviewText: The cereal has a nice flavor. Very crispy right at first but tends to get soggy pretty quick.

reviews.Title: Tasty, crunchy, yummy!
reviews.ReviewText: Great Grains Crunchy Pecan is a new favorite. The generous serving size is chock full of tasty flakes, crunchy clusters and lots of large pecan pieces. Lots of protein helps me start my day right. The only caveat was the flake got soggy quickly in milk, still had good flavor ad the crunch of the clusters and pecans helped.

reviews.Title: Yummy
reviews.ReviewText: Tastes really good and healthy. Not cardboard at all like so many grain cereals are. Love the chunks of yummy in each and every bite!

reviews.Title: Crispy and Crunchy
reviews.ReviewText: I like the way this cereal stayed crispy, instead of getting soggy. The pecans were delicious and the combination of the the different seeds and nuts was very interesting. You get clusters and then individual seeds and nuts.

reviews.Title: Great Grains
reviews.ReviewText: Love it ! The flakes are crisp stay crunchy the you get the pecans and the cluster wonderful blend of textures can't wait to try them all.

reviews.Title: crunchy, not too sweet
reviews.ReviewText: the cereal was extra crunchy, the pecan were tasty. I felt it needed more clusters

reviews.Title: Great cereal!
reviews.ReviewText: Thank you for the box of Great Grains cereal! I will definitely add that to my grocery list. Tasted great!

reviews.Title: Delicious hearty cereal
reviews.ReviewText: Crunchy pecan is delicious. Amazing flavor. I love the pieces of pecan. It's sweet but not overpowering at all. I have tried it with both almond milk and regular and it's great either way! The mixture of pecans, crunchy clusters, and oats is an amazing combo that makes for a great start to the morning!

reviews.Title: Tasty and filling!
reviews.ReviewText: This cereal is substantial. One bowl filled me up for the morning. The combination of clusters, flakes and pecans is a tasty one! There is little sweetness to this cereal, but the natural taste is fantastic. And with 5 g of fiber and 38 g of whole grains, you can be sure that it's a healthy start to your day! Recommended!

reviews.Title: Great Grains Crunchy Pecan
reviews.ReviewText: Loved the sweet pecan flavor. Stayed crunchy all the way to the bottom of the bowl. Continuing to enjoy this cereal as one of my breakfast choices!

reviews.Title: Cereal that's a healthy meal
reviews.ReviewText: I have eaten Great Grains before and forgot how wonderfully healthy and filling it is. So many health benefits in such a variety of grains and in such a small package. Great Grains is Healthy, fills you up, with a lasting pleasure you know you are eating well. Cold milk and crunch. There can't be a better way to start your day.

reviews.Title: Tasty granola type cereal
reviews.ReviewText: My box of Great Grains Crunch Pecan cereal came while I am self isolating due to the virus. I am a senior and on Day 15 as I write this review. When the cereal came I thought OH GREAT, I have no milk. BUT...I do have yogurt. Every morning for the last 3 mornings I have mixed the granola like cereal with my yogurt. IT IS DELICIOUS and I absolutely love it. What a great addition to my morning!

reviews.Title: Tastes Great
reviews.ReviewText: I like the taste and consistency of the cereal and even sometimes ate it right out of the box! I also like that it has a lot of fiber. The only thing I don't like is that there is sugar in it. It would be better if it was sweetened with stevia which even diabetics can ingest. No sweetener would be good too, so consumers could add their own preferred sweetener.

reviews.Title: Great Grains, GREAT CRUNCH !!!
reviews.ReviewText: We love it! Love the variety of ingredients and this WILL be on our shopping list. Really goes well with the almond milk we use on our cereal. Love the crunch

reviews.Title: Pecan crunchy goodness!
reviews.ReviewText: I'm really enjoying Great Grains Crunchy Pecan variety. It has a nice assortment of grains, nuts and nice large clusters and doesn't get soggy quickly. It's not too sweet and I like that it has good nutritional value without being overloaded in sugar, fat and sodium. I would definitely recommend this to others and look forward to trying the other varieties of Great Grains.

reviews.Title: Love the different textures
reviews.ReviewText: Post Great Grains Crunchy Pecan Cereal is very good, not too sweet. I love the different textures, my only complaint is that the clusters are a little too big and being too big are a distraction. If they were a little smaller, I think, the textures would blend better. I am a pecan lover and this cereal made me happy.

reviews.Title: Full of Nuts and Crunch
reviews.ReviewText: I really like this Great Grains cereal. I goes great with milk and stays crunchy. A wholesome part of my day that tastes great and makes me feel good.

reviews.Title: Tasty!
reviews.ReviewText: This cereal was very good. Lots of pecans, crunchy clusters and flakes. I would prefer that it be a little sweeter, but it still tasted good. I love that they did not skimp on the pecans and that is has lots of vitamins and fiber.

reviews.Title: Tasty and filling
reviews.ReviewText: Great Grains crunchy pecan cereal was full of flavor. I am not sure if the pecans or the clusters were my favorite! The flakes stayed tasty and not soggy at all. It kept me full for hours. I only wish the box was bigger because now I have to go out to buy more!

reviews.Title: Tasty and Crunchy
reviews.ReviewText: The pecans in the Great Grains Crunchy Pecan cereal makes the taste amazing, just the right amount of crunch and flavor. It's even good warmed in the microwave with milk, and you can add honey or maple syrup to make it a hot cereal, almost like eating a crunchy pecan pie. You could also use it in yogurt, or as a struesel topping for baking, on top of ice cream, the uses are endless!

reviews.Title: Great Grains
reviews.ReviewText: We loved it. Taste great.

reviews.Title: great taste
reviews.ReviewText: great chewy texture, good taste, I prefer my cereal a little sweeter, but adding a LITTLE (not a lot) of sweetner made it better

reviews.Title: Great tastes!
reviews.ReviewText: Awesome tasting cereal that smells great!

reviews.Title: Finally! A cereal I'd actually eat more than once.
reviews.ReviewText: I don't usually eat cereal because I don't like how it just mushes up almost as soon as the milk hits it. This cereal is the exception! Not only does it stand up to milk, retaining its crunchiness to the last bite, it also has a lot of texture and flavor; it doesn't float to the top of the milk, it soaks it up and maintains its structure. I love the mixture of textures offered by the clusters, pecans and flakes; and the flavor is very satisfying. This is a cereal I actually love and will buy.

reviews.Title: A little bit of so many good things!
reviews.ReviewText: Love the Great Grains Crunchy Pecan from first bite to the last bite! Stayed crunchy in milk as I ate it and I believe it would've stayed crunchy even longer, but it was so good, it didn't take me long to eat the whole bowl! The perfect combo of crunchy and sweet, without being to sweet. I felt full and satisfied and that there was so many good things in each bite!

reviews.Title: Versatile and Delicious
reviews.ReviewText: I love Great Grains Crunchy Pecan! It is flavorful and stays crunchy whether you have it as a traditional cereal with milk or mix it with Yogurt or peanut butter for a treat.

reviews.Title: Crunchy and Tasty
reviews.ReviewText: Delicious and crunchy, loads of nuts and grains to make it healthy and filling

reviews.Title: Delish!!!!
reviews.ReviewText: Really enjoyed this cereal. The flake to cluster/pecan ratio kept it from being too dry and tasteless, like some of the competitors.

reviews.Title: Eating healthier
reviews.ReviewText: I love the texture and mixing of flavors. I believe this product will raise my fiber levels. I will be trying the other flavors.

reviews.Title: A great bowl of goodness!
reviews.ReviewText: Today, I tried Great Grains in the Crunchy Pecan flavor. I was very interested in trying it. The nutritional information on the box looked like a cereal that would provide me with a good start to my morning. I poured my bowl added some milk and sat down to enjoy. It was very delicious. It was just the right amount of sweetness. The crunch of the clusters and pecans were delightful. The flakes did not get soggy, which sould be a deal breaker for me. I would recommend to friends and family. I would also like to try other flavors.

reviews.Title: Great Grains
reviews.ReviewText: I would have to say after giving Great Grains a try that i didnt find them to my liking so much. Yes they have all the Ingredients, like clusters, pecans, and oats. You do get some of the crunch but i think if the cereal had wheat flakes it would hold up better with the crunchy ingredients. The cereal overall was ok... Thank you Bzzz for the opportunity to give them a try.

reviews.Title: Can I give ten stars?
reviews.ReviewText: Oh!s has kept me going through the tough times in life. Oh!s has taught me that no matter what things look like on the outside, it's what's inside that counts. You might look at Oh!s and think it's just a run of the mill cereal, but then you bite into a crunchy spoonful and realize that there might just be more to life. You're treated to a delicious combination of graham, oats, and sweetness surrounded by hug of honey and joy. Thank you for inventing this cereal. The world is better because of it.

reviews.Title: Cheerios Honey Nut Breakfast Cereal Review
reviews.ReviewText: An easy to eat, crunchy, nutritious breakfast cereal

Recently after some stomach issues and having a lot of problems with digestion I began purchasing Honey Nut Cheerios to eat for breakfast in hopes that it would be gentle on my stomach. I have been very impressed because they sat really well even with all my digestion issues. They keep me filled up for a few hours and do not cause me agony. The taste is consistently great and I am happy to be getting in some whole grains. The 10.8 oz box is skinny and just short enough to fit in our Manhattan cabinet with ease. I will continue to use these in the future. 

When you purchase be sure to check Target Circle as thy sometimes offer additional discounts and MFR coupons!

reviews.Title: It reminds me of childhood, so I like it.
reviews.ReviewText: I first tried this cereal when I was an extremely young child, my mother gave me a small bag of it dry to keep me occupied while she worked on speaking to someone. My only memory that accompanies that is that I loved the texture and flavor, it was just a satisfying snack. After that I had completely forgotten about it, until one day I had a random craving. Now I hadn't thought about this cereal for so long, it turned out I completely about this cereal, but I craved the nostalgia of that memory, the satisfying crunch, and the familiar flavor. After a few months, I thought I was going crazy as I couldn't remember the what the darn thing even looked like. Eventually after a few rounds of cereal roulette, I had found this box. I was a bit disheartened to find that the taste had changed a bit, but that may be more the fault of my aging tongue rather than the formula or really anything in General Mills part. I eat this cereal in the morning best paired with 2% milk, as to not heavily out weigh milk to cereal flavor. Then I usually put a small amount in sandwich bag to take with me to work. The look of this cereal allows me to eat these as a snack without really being judged, since it doesn't look like typical cereal. This cereal is one of my favorites, if not my absolute favorite for bringing me a moment of the past back into my day to day trudge.

reviews.Title: No More BHT!

They also improved their packaging and I was happy to easily open the plastic bag without it ripping down the side.

reviews.Title: Not good
reviews.ReviewText: These are not good at all. I tried them when they first came out several years ago and they were pretty good but still lacking. They have changed the recipe. They used to consist of about half actual chocolate cheerios, and half chocolate coated cereal and the coating tasted exactly like Coco Puffs. Now they are fully “chocolate” Cheerios meaning that the whole Cheerio is chocolate flavored and not just coated. They do have a light sweetened coating that tastes nothing like coco puffs like before. They barely have a chocolate flavor at all. I like that they aren’t super sweet though. Coco puffs and chocolate cheerios have the roughly the same amount of calories (100) for the same serving size of 3/4 cup, if you want a chocolate flavored cereal just go for the puffs.

reviews.Title: What Have You Done to my Cereal? - Part 2 - A Happy Ending
reviews.ReviewText: From ONE STAR to FIVE STARS - I have to agree with "al" from VA... I bought a box of my favorite Great Grains cereal, Raisins, Dates & Pecans a few months ago, as I always do. But when I got home, I noticed a banner on the box that said "New Improved Flavor." I never thought there was anything wrong with the original flavor. I was immediately disappointed to discover the "improved" flavor made the cereal tasted like a bowl full of chemicals. And there was a dusty residue on the flakes that remained in the bowl. Just yucky. So, reluctantly, I stopped buying it. But a few days ago, I noticed that the banner had been removed from the front of the box. Hmmm... did this mean that the "new improved flavor" is not new anymore so no need to announce it? Or, hopefully, did it meant that enough people complained about it so the company restored the original recipe? I am happy to report that this box of cereal tastes just like the original I remember! Not sure what happened here, but thank you for going back to the original flavor and texture! No need for improvements here!

reviews.Title: What have you done to my favorite cereal?

Let me know if you go back to your previous recipe. .

reviews.Title: False Flakes
reviews.ReviewText: I have always been a fan of great grains cereals primarily because of the small flake whole grains. The introduction of large flakes without any clear, obvious notification on the box is very unprofessional. Ordering online during the pandemic, it is impossible to differentiate between, say, Raisins, Dates, Pecans (which are the traditional small flake grains) and Cranberry Almond Crunch. There is nothing on the box indicating the difference in consistency—they both say "Flakes and Clusters" .The cranberry almond crunch is like every other cereal on the market. Very tricky marketing and totally unprofessional. This could be solved by clearly indicating the grain flake size on the box so that online shoppers could order the correct product. Get it together marketing, I don't have time to police my cereal purchases.

reviews.Title: I will not buy this cereal anymore

If you wanted to make a new cereal that's fine. But you put this new cereal in a box we are all familiar with and tricked us into buying it. Bring back the cereal we all love, please.

reviews.Title: Favorite Cereal

The flakes are crunchy even after adding milk the cereal stays crunchy and not soggy at all. For me as a diabetic I like the fact that there is not a lot of sugar but still loads of flavor. I also like the fact that you can eat a whole cup as a serving and feel full when you are done eating. 7g of fiber is excellent considering all the great flavor this cereal has. I will definitely buy the Banana nut crunch cereal and would love to try the other flavors as well. On facebook and when we are allowed out in public again I would definitely share my feelings with friends and family about what a great product Post Great Grains Cereal is.

reviews.Title: Wonderful!, WOW!
reviews.ReviewText: "Received it free",Post's Great Grains Cereal is not your grandmother's cereal. How is it different? Right out of the box, it bursts with flavor. But in milk, now that's where Post's Great Grains Cereal comes alive and showcases its turbo-charged flavor. Right away the almonds and walnuts demonstrate why the stomach and taste buds slap each other a hi-five the moment the box is opened. It's true the Almonds and Walnuts are sufficient to satisfy the most demanding breakfast pallet, but there's something more; something that the most finicky child cannot resist. It's the goodness of the banana clusters. And if that wasn't enough, the toasted flakes don't go limp moments after they splash around in the milk. So, if you are searching for a cereal that can unite the whole family's taste buds, pick up a box, better make it two,

reviews.Title: My old favorite!
reviews.ReviewText: My continued purchases of Pumpkin Flax Granola speaks for itself. I happily consume it at breakfast everyday. I also use the granola to sprinkle on salads. There is one characteristic that I think would make sense for the product; a lower sugar content option for those that are concerned about sugar intake. I am not diabetic so that is not an issue for me but a lowered caloric version of the cereal would be welcome. After all, there are 10g of sugar per serving (3/4 of a cup renders 260 calories). Couldn't the sugar be cut back to reduce the caloric intake? Yes, there are calories attributable to the fat in the granola but I do not know how many calories come form added sugar versus the calories that come form the fat content of the granola. So, how about a " Pumpkin Seed-Flax Granola "Lite" to offer an even healthier product?

reviews.Title: My FORMER favorite granola cereal
reviews.ReviewText: This had been one of my favorite organic breakfast cereals. However, with "Inc. Added Sugars" it is now sickeningly too sweet. Given the obesity crisis in America and the proliferation of Diabetes 1 and 2 and simply from a taste standpoint the "Added Sugars" make no sense at all. The previous sugar content was ok. Will discontinue purchasing this cereal. The "Inc. Added Sugars" comment also applies to the other Nature's Path organic granola cereals. I hope that "Nature's Path" will reconsider the whole idea of "Inc. Added Sugars" and return to what is actually healthy for America.

reviews.Title: As good as always!!
reviews.ReviewText: I do not agree with some of the negative reviews I just read. Based on the nutrition facts table, there is nowhere near 1038 kcals in a cup. But if you want to eat Honey Bunches of Oats, you will get more junk (i.e. COLOUR, BARLEY MALT EXTRACT, NATURAL AND ARTIFICIAL FLAVOUR, BHT), sodium (200 mg versus 45 mg) and less fiber (3g versus 5g in a serving). The sugar content by the way is comparable about 10 grams/serving for both. I don't think you would have to eat as much of this cereal to feel fuller, longer. That's a plus in my books. In Canada the quality of the cereal is the same as the first box I bought. And I've consumed a lot of boxes over the years. My only complaint is that it has gone up in price.

reviews.Title: A bit misleading
reviews.ReviewText: While the cereal itself is great, there is nothing in the ingredient list or in the pictures to indicate that half of what you'll pour in your bowl is puffed rice. I purchased a granola cereal, not a puffed rice cereal. The price difference between the 2 is substantial, and just to add filler but charge granola cereal pricing is a cheap way to conduct business. It was on special at the supermarket, so I bought 2 boxes. If I knew puffed rice was a major part of my purchase, it would have been 1 box of the pumpkin flax and 1 package of puffed rice cereal. By volume I would have come out ahead.

reviews.Title: A LOT less product in bag than advertised.
reviews.ReviewText: I recently purchased a 23.8 oz bag of the Sunrise Crunchy Vanilla. I'm currently working on portion control, so once I got home I started bagging per serving size (says 2/3cup per serving on bag). While the bag says about 23 servings per container, I only have 15 serving in my bag... that is QUITE A DIFFERENCE!!! The cereal itself is good, a little high in sugars for my liking, but at least its organic and I know what's in it. Still debating if I will purchase again.

reviews.Title: Crunchy and yummy!
reviews.ReviewText: The "Crunchy Vanilla Sunrise" has three different cereals all packed into one. You have the flakes, cereal puffs, and little rice cereal pieces. The cereal is a crunchy one (due to the flakes and cereal puffs the most). One problem with the "Crunchy Vanilla Sunrise" was that it was a little sweet for my liking. The flavor also seemed odd as well (not in a bad way). It might be because of the sweetness though because sweet foods have always tasted odd, flavorless and not so tasty to me. However I was able to finish the amount I poured into my bowl and used an unsweetened milk alternative with the cereal. This though is a cereal I would definitely get again. This cereal is perfect for those looking for a crunchy texture.

reviews.Title: New ingredient and taste with "New Look"
reviews.ReviewText: This was my favorite gluten free cereal! I probably went through 2-3 boxes a week. I just poured a bowl and immediately noticed a change in size, texture and flavor of the cereal. It doesn't even taste like peanut butter. I went to check the new box and compared it with my old box and realized that the ingredients were different. The "New Look" boxes have a new ingredient, tapioca starch. I have a moderate inflammatory response when I eat tapioca anything. Hopefully in the future with "New Look" they will also mention a change in ingredients. Luckily I don't have a severe allergy, but eating a little before I noticed will probably have some uncomfortable consequences . I am so sad that my favorite cereal no longer tastes good or is okay for me to eat.

reviews.Title: Consider me a cereal convert...
reviews.ReviewText: I've never been much of a cereal eater, as I've always found I need something more substantial in the morning to keep the hangries away for more than a few hours. I picked up Panda Puffs on a whim, more for a celiac-friendly snack than for a meal, and ended up devouring the box. Not only is this absolutely delicious, but I've found I can eat it for breakfast and it actually fills me up! As others have said, it's not too sweet, either. This may have a cartoon panda on the box...but it's definitely adult approved! As a side note, I've ordered Panda Puffs direct from Nature's Path several times now and the shipping is super fast. I order in bulk and the products have all been fresh with many months to spare on the expiration date. I'm very pleased all around!
